==English==

===Noun===
'''[[double]] [[negative]]'''
# A phrase in which there are two points of negation in a sentence, often leading to [[ambiguity]] in the meaning, but necessary in some foreign languages.

====Examples in English====
#:''Jimmy, you look awfully guilty, have you been naughty again?''
#:''Me sir, no sir, I haven't done nothing wrong, I swear.'' 

